<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="refuse-v">refuse <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /rɪ'fjuːz/    美 /rɪ'fjuːz/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-turn-down">1.★ <strong>拒绝；回绝 (turn down)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>refuse an invitation
拒绝邀请</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If given something you don’t want to eat, just refuse politely. 
如果别人给你一些你不想吃的东西，你就礼貌地拒绝。</p><footer>外研⑦ – 5</footer></div>

<ul>
<li>refuse to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He refused to discuss things further. 
他不愿意进一步讨论这些事。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>refusal /rɪ'fjuːzl/ n   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Alice wanted to borrow Jack’s computer, but he <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (拒绝).  （2012 全国）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. refused  </p></div>